dcterms:creator: P. J. Bentley

dcterms:description: COIL is a hybrid machine learning and optimization approach designed to learn valid regions of the search space for constrained optimization problems, specifically applied to scheduling autonomous robots for home delivery.
dcterms:title: COIL (Constrained Optimization in Learned Latent Space)

dcterms:creator: P. J. Bentley
S. L. Lim
A. Gaier
L. Tran
dcterms:description: SOLVE is an approach that utilizes latent variable evolution to optimize search spaces, focusing on improving the efficiency of search algorithms in constrained environments.
dcterms:title: SOLVE (Search Space Optimization with Latent Variable Evolution)

dcterms:creator: G. E. Hinton
R. R. Salakhutdinov
dcterms:description: This dataset is used for dimensionality reduction through neural networks, demonstrating how neural networks can effectively reduce the dimensionality of data while preserving its structure.
dcterms:title: Neural Networks (for dimensionality reduction)

dcterms:creator: D. P. Kingma
M. Welling
dcterms:description: The Variational Autoencoder (VAE) is a generative model that learns to represent data in a latent space, allowing for efficient sampling and reconstruction of data.
dcterms:title: Variational Autoencoder (VAE)
